          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "-Neutron capture cross-section ratios of Pu-240 and",
                " Pu-242 versus Au-197 in the energy range from 50",
                " to 250 keV-"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "VDG"
                ],
                "institute": "2GERKFK"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Karlsruhe 3 MV pulsed accelerator",
                "provided  protons with pulse width of 700 psec,with a",
                "repetition  rate of 5 MHz,with an average current of",
                "15 microA.  The proton energy was chosen 100 keV",
                "above the  n-source reaction threshold at 1019 keV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "P-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The water-cooled neutron target consisted of",
                " a tritium loaded titanium layer(12.5mm diam,2.1micron",
                " thick),evaporated onto a 0.3 mm thick tungsten",
                " backing and protected by an evaporated layer of",
                " 50 micrograms/cm**2 aluminium.",
                ".The specific target activity was 0.8 Ci/cm2.",
                ".the energy range of neutrons was up to 250 keV.",
                ".All neutrons were emitted from the target into a",
                " cone in forward direction with an opening angle",
                " of 120 degrees."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".The following table summarizes the relevant sample",
                " data.(For the chemical and isotopic composition see",
                " NSE,66)",
                "  sample meas.No weight(g) thickness(atom/b)",
                " Pu-240   1,2   3.038     0.000952",
                " Pu-242    1    10.705    0.00333",
                "           2    8.744     0.00272",
                " Au-197    1    13.545    0.00586",
                "           2    13.209    0.00571",
                " U-235     1    7.649     0.00277",
                "           2    9.066     0.00328",
                " graphite  1    0.547     0.00388 canned,dummy(240)",
                "                1.55      0.0110  canned,dummy(242)",
                "                2.02      0.0143  uncanned,dummy(197)",
                "           2    1.778     0.0126  canned,dummy."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " With kinematically collimated neutrons due to",
                " the center-of-mass movement of the compound nucleus.",
                ".The flight path was 65 mm long.",
                ".A set of four samples were mounted on a sample changer",
                " and cycled automatically into the measuring position.",
                " The cycle time was determined by integrating the beam",
                " current to a preselected charge.",
                ".A dummy sample was used to correct for background",
                " events and a U-235 sample served for normalization",
                " of the fission correction.",
                ".The capture cross-section ratios of Pu versus Au-197",
                " have been measured twice for each isotope.In the",
                " first measurement a metallic Au-197 disc was used",
                " while in the second one it was canned in a",
                " polyethylene foil to avoid against neutron scattering",
                " in the envelope of Pu samples.",
                ".The parameters of the individual measurements are",
                " as follows,I to IV runs for 1st meas,V and VI for 2nd,",
                " run sample1 sample2 sample3 sample4 MNE(keV) F.P.(mm)",
                " I   Pu-240  dummy0  U-235   Au-197  210.     66.0",
                " II  Pu-242  dummy2  U-235   Au-197  250.     66.0",
                " III dummy0    -     U-235   dummy7  250.     66.0",
                " IV  dummy7  Au-197  Au-197C dummy7C 250.     62.8",
                " V   Pu-240  dummy   Au-197C U-235   250.     66.0",
                " VI  Pu-242  dummy   Au-197C U-235   250.     67.6",
                ".the MNE is the maximum neutron energy,F.P.-the flight",
                " path,dummy0 the dummy sample for Pu-240,dummy2 for",
                " Pu-242,dummy7 for Au-197 suffix C means canned with",
                " polyethylene foil."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MOXR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " With a 25 mm thick graphite converter used for",
                " registration of gamma-rays from capture and fission",
                " events"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " fission neutron detector using a NE-213",
                " liquid scintillator with pulse-shape discriminator",
                " equipment,used to correct data for fission events.",
                ".Both detectors were shielded with lead and were",
                " located at backward angles of 120 deg with respect",
                " to the beam axis.They were completely outside the",
                " neutron cone."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
